# Conventional Commit template for A2A Digital Twin
#
# Format:
#   <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Allowed types:
#   feat     New user-visible behavior
#   fix      Bug fix
#   ci       CI/CD pipeline or automation changes
#   build    Build system or dependency changes
#   refactor Internal code change without behavior change
#   test     Test-only changes
#   docs     Documentation-only changes
#   chore    Maintenance that does not fit other types
#   perf     Performance improvements
#   revert   Revert a previous commit
#
# Subject rules:
# - Use imperative mood (e.g., "add", "fix", "update")
# - No trailing period
# - Target <= 72 characters
#
# Example:
#   ci(webhook): route dispatch to production workflow
#
# Optional body/footer sections for automation:
# Why:
# - <why this change is needed>
#
# What changed:
# - <behavior/code changes introduced>
#
# Validation:
# - <tests/checks/commands run>
#
# Refs: #123
# BREAKING CHANGE: <describe incompatible API or behavior change>

<type>(<scope>): <subject>

# Why:
# -
#
# What changed:
# -
#
# Validation:
# -
#
# Refs: #
# BREAKING CHANGE:
